HEADWORD: Pasteurism
<hw>Pas*teur"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Fr.
<etsep>Pasteur</etsep>, a French scientist.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
method of treatment, devised by <persfn>Pasteur</persfn>, for preventing
certain diseases, as hydrophobia, by successive inoculations with an
attenuated virus of gradually increasing strength.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pasteurization.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasteurization</ent>⟦br⟧
